race.comment: NEPELA (1) wound up strongly to just miss last start at Wodonga and looks ready to peak fourth-up. Can offset the wide draw early and could prove tough to catch. BOLD TRIUMPH (2) disappointed here last time but was a determined winner two back at Corowa. Boasts a solid record at the course and distance and is drawn to advantage, making him a big threat. TRIFECTA RUBY (7) doesn't win often but has a strong record on her home track and usually runs well at this trip. Gets in well with the claim and looms as a serious chance. INCANTATA (13) was solid when resuming at Corowa, sticking on into midfield. Sure to improve and holds intrigue on the quick back-up. LOVEOFMYLIFE (5) failed last time but her prior efforts were competitive against subsequent winners. Worth keeping safe.
